commit.message: cli: bugzilla search: tweak --quicksearch value name

rework request parameter creation

Among other things, this allows supporting search templates and
serializing requests.

Fixes #19.
lib: bugzilla: drop support for loading request params from files
cli: github search: drop unused parameters serialization support
cargo: update dep versions
cli: redmine search: only allow --order to be used a single time
cli: redmine search: add separate search options struct
cli: redmine search: add -n/--dry-run option support
cli: redmine search: only support single value for --fields

bugzilla search: use singular values for status queries
bugzilla search: support logical OR/AND ops for keywords
bugzilla search: support logical OR/AND ops for groups
bugzilla search: support logical OR/AND for personal tag queries

cli: bugzilla search: don't allow multiple options for --fields or --order

Only CSV values are allowed to specify multiple values.

cli: bugzilla search: don't support CSV for singular values

CSV values imply logical AND which doesn't make sense for singular
fields.

bugzilla search: make --id consistent with other logical OR options

In that multiple options need to used instead of comma-separated values
which refer to logical AND.

Also, support inverted ID queries via negative numbers similar to the
blocks and depends options.
cli: bugzilla search: convert user values to Match during parsing
lib: implement IntoIterator for Csv
bugzilla search: explicitly use Csv wrappers for relevant values
bugzilla search: support logical operators for flags values
bugzilla search: support logical operators for alias values
bugzilla search: support logical operators for blocks and depends
bugzilla search: simplify blocks and depends values using signed integers

bugzilla search: make user-related query functions target single users

Using public logical op functions to combine multiple values.

bugzilla search: add initial support for OR/AND ops for relevant user fields

Fixes #37.
bugzilla search: use singular names for user options
